Sir Ranulph Fiennes has become the oldest Briton to complete the Marathon des Sables in the desert . 
  The 71-year-old completed the 256km race through the Moroccan desert with just 13 minutes to spare . 
  He has previously suffered two heart attacks and underwent a double heart bypass in 2003 . 
  There were fears he would not finish after the 91km fourth stage . 
  He ran for more than 30 hours in temperatures topping 50C and had just one hour of sleep . 
